# SDD State Directory Conventions

## Directory Structure

```
.sdd/
├── state/<feature>.json              # Feature state (single source of truth for workflow position)
├── summaries/<feature>/<phase>-summary.md  # Phase summaries (read these first)
├── handoffs/<feature>/<from>-to-<to>.md    # Structured context between agents
├── workspace/<feature>/current/<phase>.md  # Active draft artifacts
├── workspace/<feature>/implementation/     # Task board, worker assignments, code outputs
└── registry/<feature>/<phase>/vN.md        # Approved immutable versioned artifacts
```

## Feature State JSON Schema

```json
{
  "feature": "<feature-name>",
  "mode": "manual | guided | delegated",
  "current_phase": "<phase>",
  "status": "in_progress | waiting_for_approval | approved | fail | escalated | done",
  "approved_phases": ["idea", "spec", ...],
  "workers": 1,
  "validators": 1,
  "registry_versions": { "<phase>": <version_number> },
  "blocking_findings": [],
  "created_at": "<ISO timestamp>",
  "updated_at": "<ISO timestamp>"
}
```

Update `updated_at` on every state change. Advance `current_phase` only after human approval.

## Summaries

Use the summary template: Phase, What Was Produced, Key Decisions, Risks/Open Issues, What the Next Agent Must Know. Keep concise — this is the primary input for the next phase.

## Handoffs

Use the handoff template: Feature, From/To agent, Completed Work (paths), Key Decisions, Constraints to Preserve, Risks, Recommended Next Action.

## Registry

- Only approved artifacts go in `registry/`. Drafts stay in `workspace/`.
- Version naming: `v1.md`, `v2.md`, etc. Increment on re-approval after rework.
- Registry artifacts are immutable. Never edit a versioned file — create a new version instead.
